comments.content: That looks like the NatWest typeface, which I believe is custom. I'm not certain though...

Post your request at the [Type Identification Board](http://web.archive.org/web/20080228132929/http:/www.typophile.com/forums/messages/83/83.html?1089669273), John.   
We'll be able to help you way better over there.

If it is the Nat West typeface, and it does look like it, it is a custom named NatWest.   
Tim
